---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '@/components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service, Meld"
  description="The terms of using the Meld waitlist and website."
>
  <Nav slot="nav" />

  <article class="legal section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <header class="legal-header">
        <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="h1">Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="meta">
          <strong>Effective:</strong> April 11, 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp;
          <strong>Last updated:</strong> April 11, 2026
        </p>
      </header>

      <p>
        These Terms of Service are a legal agreement between you and Meld. They apply when
        you visit heymeld.com, join our waitlist, or use the Meld iOS app once it is
        available. By using our website or services, you agree to these Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>1. What Meld is</h2>
      <p>
        Meld is a consumer wellness product being built by Brock Howard. As of today, Meld
        operates a pre-launch marketing website at heymeld.com with a waitlist for the
        forthcoming iOS app. The app is not yet available for download.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Not a medical device</h2>
      <p>
        This is important. Meld is a wellness and coaching product, not a medical device.
        Meld is not designed to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. Meld does not
        replace advice from a qualified health professional.
      </p>
      <p>
        Always consult your doctor before changing your diet, exercise, supplements,
        medications, or medical routine based on anything Meld shows you. In an emergency,
        call emergency services. If you or someone you know is in emotional crisis, contact
        the 988 Suicide &amp; Crisis Lifeline (call or text 988) or the Crisis Text Line
        (text HOME to 741741). Do not use Meld for urgent medical needs. Never ignore
        professional medical advice because of something Meld told you.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Your account</h2>
      <p>
        You can join the waitlist by submitting your email. When the full app launches, you
        will be asked to create an account. You must provide accurate information, keep your
        account secure, be at least 13 years old or the minimum age in your country
        (whichever is higher), and only use Meld for your own body.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>
        You agree not to use Meld for anyone other than yourself. You agree not to scrape,
        copy, or redistribute Meld's content or the coach's responses without permission.
        You agree not to reverse engineer the app or backend. You agree not to access other
        users' data. You agree not to upload anything illegal, harmful, or that violates
        anyone's rights. You agree not to try to make the coach give you dangerous, harmful,
        or illegal advice. You agree not to use Meld to impersonate a licensed professional.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Waitlist</h2>
      <p>
        Joining the waitlist does not guarantee access to the app. We cannot promise a
        specific launch date. We will email you when access is available. You can
        unsubscribe from the waitlist at any time.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        Meld's name, logo, website, app, and all original content belong to us. You may
        link to heymeld.com and share our public content. You may not reproduce our brand or
        content commercially without written permission.
      </p>
      <p>Your data belongs to you. See our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for details.</p>

      <h2>7. AI disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        Meld uses AI, specifically Anthropic's Claude, to power the coach. AI can make
        mistakes. Do not treat coach responses as the final word. Always use common sense,
        and consult a qualified professional for medical decisions. We do our best to ground
        coaching in published research, but we do not guarantee accuracy, completeness, or
        suitability for your specific situation.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
      <p>
        Meld is provided as is, without warranty of any kind, express or implied. We do not
        warrant that Meld will be uninterrupted, secure, or error free. We do not warrant
        that the results from using Meld will meet your health goals. We do not warrant that
        the coach's advice is perfectly accurate for your specific situation. We do not
        warrant that any errors in content will be corrected.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, Meld and its founders are not liable for any
        indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your
        use of the website, waitlist, or app. Our total liability for any claim will not
        exceed one hundred US dollars or the amount you paid us in the past twelve months,
        whichever is greater.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Changes to these Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms. We will post the new version here and update the Last
        Updated date. Material changes will be announced by email to waitlist members.
        Continued use of Meld after a change means you accept the new Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Governing law</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by the laws of the United States and the state where Meld
        is incorporated, which will be confirmed before launch. Disputes will be resolved in
        the courts of that state.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these Terms? Email
        <a href="mailto:hello@heymeld.com">hello@heymeld.com</a>. We reply within a few
        business days.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal {
    background: var(--bg-primary);
  }

  .legal-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-12);
  }

  .legal-header .h1 {
    margin-block: var(--sp-2) var(--sp-4);
  }

  .legal .meta {
    font-size: var(--fs-body-sm);
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
  }

  .legal .prose h2 {
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: var(--fw-regular);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-top: var(--sp-10);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .legal .prose p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-weight: var(--fw-light);
    line-height: var(--lh-relaxed);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
  }
</style>
